sql:
SELECT v.variant_id, sg.snp_gene_name
FROM variants v
JOIN snp_gene_ids sg ON v.variant_id = sg.variant_id;

SELECT snp_gene_name, snp_gene_description 
FROM snp_gene_ids 
WHERE variant_id = 0;

SELECT genotyping_technology_name, genotyping_technology_description 
FROM genotyping_technology 
ORDER BY genotyping_technology_name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- Well-characterized studies imply that they have detailed information or data in associated tables; 
- Genetic associations refer to the connections or relationships between genetic variants and traits or conditions found in the associations table;
- Successfully passed quality control means that the studies involve platforms where more than zero SNPs have passed quality checks, indicating a level of reliability in the data.

sql:
SELECT upstream_gene_id, variant_id, upstream_gene_description
FROM upstream_genes 
WHERE upstream_gene_name LIKE '%downstream%';

SELECT study_title, first_author
FROM studies
ORDER BY publication_date DESC;
